## Seeders base

```
DatabaseSeeder
├── EnterprisePermissionSeeder        -- 11 permisos enterprise base
├── EnterpriseRoleSeeder              -- owner, admin, member, billing (enterprise_id null)
├── EnterpriseRolePermissionSeeder    -- asigna permisos a roles globales; owner tiene todos
├── WorkspacePermissionSeeder         -- permisos workspace base
├── PlanSeeder                        -- Personal Free, Personal Pro, Enterprise Free, Enterprise Pro, Enterprise
└── AdminUserSeeder                   -- solo entorno dev (excluido de tests)
```

Los primeros cinco son **seeders de catálogo** — datos que el código asume que siempre existen.
Se ejecutan antes de cada suite en `tests/Pest.php`.

### Permisos enterprise

11 permisos definidos en `EnterprisePermissionSeeder`:
`enterprise.settings.view/edit`, `enterprise.members.view/invite/remove`,
`enterprise.roles.manage`, `enterprise.billing.view/manage`,
`workspace.create/delete`, `workspace.members.invite_external`

### Asignación rol → permisos (`EnterpriseRolePermissionSeeder`)

| Rol | Permisos |
|---|---|
| `owner` | todos (11) |
| `admin` | settings.view/edit, members.view/invite/remove, billing.view, workspace.create/delete, workspace.members.invite_external |
| `member` | settings.view, members.view, workspace.create |
| `billing` | settings.view, billing.view, billing.manage |

El rol `owner` es inmutable — ver regla en `docs/stages/09-enterprises.mdc`.

